Reasoning: The paper deals with robot manipulation problems and planning dexterous reach-to-grasp trajectories under object pose uncertainty. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses a belief space planning approach, which involves probabilistic reasoning and decision-making, indicating that it could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of point clouds and 6D non-Gaussian distributions suggests that the paper could also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also involves experimental results, which could indicate that it belongs to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with control problems, which could suggest that it belongs to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
